28
00:02:21,123 --> 00:02:24,925
This is a paper that has gone through the subcommittee process and through the committee of the whole process.

29
00:02:24,965 --> 00:02:33,489
And what it is, Mr. President, is it's a proposal to ensure that people that are bidding on public contracts here in the city of Medford comply with the wage and hour laws.

30
00:02:34,090 --> 00:02:47,276
It requires that a series of certifications are made and a series of statements of credibility are made to the administration so that when they're awarding a contract, the individuals that are awarded the contract have not been found in violation of any wage and hour laws.

31
00:02:48,117 --> 00:02:50,398
Wage theft is a problem across the country, Mr. President.

32
00:02:50,762 --> 00:02:55,066
It's something that we see here in Massachusetts a lot of times with contracts like cleaning contracts.

33
00:02:55,767 --> 00:03:00,852
For example, the high school has a cleaning contract, and they may bring people in to clean the high school.

34
00:03:01,393 --> 00:03:04,616
And the prevailing wage rate, which they are supposed to be paid by law, is $26 an hour.

35
00:03:06,132 --> 00:03:10,694
But these employees are hourly workers that make $18 an hour when not working on the prevailing wage.

36
00:03:10,714 --> 00:03:12,995
And their employer will withhold those funds, Mr. President.

37
00:03:13,015 --> 00:03:15,796
So they're actually employers that are stealing money from their employees.

38
00:03:16,176 --> 00:03:26,000
So this ordinance requires that people that are bidding on public projects that are covered under the prevailing wage laws and other state and federal hour and wage laws, Mr. President, are in compliance.

39
00:03:26,100 --> 00:03:29,582
They inform the city whether or not they've been found in violation.

40
00:03:29,622 --> 00:03:33,203
And they take out certain bonds if they have been found in violation.

