03:03:24,514 --> 03:03:27,735
I'm Robert Capucci, Jr., 71 Evans Street in Medford.

2218
03:03:27,795 --> 03:03:29,915
I'll try to be brief at this late hour.

2219
03:03:30,975 --> 03:03:44,459
Last summer, it was proposed that the city move towards municipal aggregation based solely on it would save the electric rate payers in Medford some money.

2220
03:03:46,299 --> 03:03:46,999
It went away.

2221
03:03:47,460 --> 03:03:49,340
Somehow it came back last Tuesday.

2222
03:03:49,925 --> 03:03:57,550
in a committee of the whole meeting under a new auspice of protecting the environment, Go Green.

2223
03:03:58,331 --> 03:04:13,201
There was a wonderful presentation brought by the company, supposedly going to be hired by Alicia Hunt, the director of energy and environment here in Medford, the chairman of the Go Green Medford community.

2224
03:04:13,981 --> 03:04:16,523
Basically, for the citizens that are watching at home,

2225
03:04:17,705 --> 03:04:32,416
It's a program whereby if passed, if it ever comes to a vote in this council and it does get passed, you're automatically opted into the city buying your power for you, your electricity, with the provision that you can opt out.

2226
03:04:34,497 --> 03:04:38,540
Understandably, what the company said last week was you can opt out at any time.

2227
03:04:39,316 --> 03:04:43,939
There was also a 30 day opt out clause in there.

2228
03:04:44,439 --> 03:04:52,984
But Councillor Marks at the committee of the whole meeting brought up the state law which is after 180 days you cannot opt out.

2229
03:04:53,325 --> 03:05:02,030
And getting into these government contracts doing things on behalf of the people, when they tell you, you know, we'll let you opt out at any time.

2230
03:05:02,871 --> 03:05:04,432
But the state losses something out.

2231
03:05:04,832 --> 03:05:21,357
I'm a little bit skeptical of the whole process I if they if this is really such a good thing They should present it and market it to the people as an as an opt-in if they want to not Force everybody all at once to be a part of this system.

2232
03:05:21,457 --> 03:05:23,177
I mean, that's a slippery slope.

2233
03:05:23,217 --> 03:05:23,777
Where does it end?

2234
03:05:24,037 --> 03:05:26,378
Is the City Council gonna vote that?

2235
03:05:28,066 --> 03:05:31,787
another company buys all my clothes from me, all my groceries.

2236
03:05:32,048 --> 03:05:35,769
It's, it's, it's, it's dangerous precedent that was sent setting.

2237
03:05:36,329 --> 03:05:36,929
It really is.

2238
03:05:37,330 --> 03:05:40,131
But I want to be fair to the other side.

2239
03:05:40,791 --> 03:05:47,494
Uh, counselor Della Russo at the committee of the whole meeting was a very astute and bringing up, I would like to hear opposition to this.

2240
03:05:47,954 --> 03:05:53,956
So I emailed everybody on this council, the citizens against municipal aggregation website.

2241
03:05:54,436 --> 03:05:56,177
I also included the mayor and,

2242
03:05:56,861 --> 03:05:59,683
Alicia hunt, the director of environment and engineer.

2243
03:06:00,183 --> 03:06:06,066
I'm also going to reach out to them if it ever does come to a vote so that the opposite side could be heard.

2244
03:06:06,726 --> 03:06:17,132
I just find it just comforting that the city would entertain the notion of doing something on behalf of every resident.

2245
03:06:18,453 --> 03:06:22,976
from reading the CAMA website, it doesn't always work.

2246
03:06:23,416 --> 03:06:29,459
And if you are locked into it, and they say you can get out, but on that 181st day, you do try to get out.

2247
03:06:29,499 --> 03:06:32,000
For some reason, you can't, and a lower rate comes.

2248
03:06:32,341 --> 03:06:35,162
I mean, you can go to the two sources now.

2249
03:06:35,202 --> 03:06:37,203
It's at Eversource and National Grid.

2250
03:06:37,603 --> 03:06:38,664
And you can click on them now.

2251
03:06:39,377 --> 03:06:42,719
